The FAT filesystem was originally created for Microsoft Windows. It has made its way over to Linux systems and has official support in the Linux kernel.

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===

{{KernelBox|title=Enable FAT support (<var>CONFIG_VFAT_FS</var>)|1=
File systems  --->
   DOS/FAT/NT Filesystems  --->
      <*> VFAT (Windows-95) fs support
      (437) Default codepage for FAT 
      (iso8859-1) Default iocharset for FAT
}}

== Usage ==

It should be possible to mount FAT filesystems with the {{c|mount}} command.

